The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Sona Koyo lines up expansion plans

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Jan 30: Sona Koyo Steering Systems plans to invest Rs 800 crore for capacity expansion till 2010.

 To gear up for the rising export potential of auto components, the company will expand its capacity to 3.5-4 million units per annum from 1 million units at present.

 Chairman and managing director Surinder Kapur said, ?The expansion will be conducted in phases over the next five years. We will expand the plant size in phases of half million units.?

 Sona Koyo is identifying special economic zones (SEZ) to expand.

 ?We are waiting for the SEZ bill to pass before taking further decisions and are currently looking at Tamil Nadu and Maharashtra,? said Kapur.

 Of the total investment, Sona Koyo has spent Rs 120 crore in 2003-04. In the current financial year, the outlay is Rs 200 crore, while for 2005-06, the investment will be Rs 280 crore. 

 The remaining amount of Rs 200 crore will be spread over the next few years till 2010.

 The entire investment till date and also for the next fiscal will be financed through internal accruals and external borrowings, said Kapur. 

 ?We have not yet considered the option of raising further capital from the stock market,? added Kapur. 




